{
  "page": "Wayn",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For other uses, see <a href=\"/index.php/Wayn_(disambiguation)\" title=\"Wayn (disambiguation)\">Wayn (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\n<p><br />\nA <b>wayn</b> is a type of <a href=\"/index.php/Wagon\" title=\"Wagon\">wagon</a> pulled by <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horses</a> or oxen, and generally used for agricultural purposes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup> A typical wayn has four wheels, but two-wheeled wayns also exist.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Folk\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Free Folk\">Free Folk</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a> uses wayns, <a href=\"/index.php/Cart\" title=\"Cart\">carts</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Sled\" title=\"Sled\">sleds</a> to transport their goods.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Wayns, carts, <a href=\"/index.php/Hathay\" title=\"Hathay\">hathays</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Palanquin\" title=\"Palanquin\">palanquins</a> are common in the streets of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/House_Wayn\" title=\"House Wayn\">House Wayn</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Waynwood\" title=\"House Waynwood\">House Waynwood</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a> both depict wheels on their sigil.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Wayn.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Wayn.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/56/House_Wayn.svg/109px-House_Wayn.svg.png\" width=\"109\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/56/House_Wayn.svg/164px-House_Wayn.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/56/House_Wayn.svg/218px-House_Wayn.svg.png 2x\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Waynwood.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Waynwood.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Waynwood.svg/109px-House_Waynwood.svg.png\" width=\"109\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Waynwood.svg/164px-House_Waynwood.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/House_Waynwood.svg/218px-House_Waynwood.svg.png 2x\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dimitri_Bielak_Riches_of_the_Reach.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e6/Dimitri_Bielak_Riches_of_the_Reach.jpg/300px-Dimitri_Bielak_Riches_of_the_Reach.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e6/Dimitri_Bielak_Riches_of_the_Reach.jpg/450px-Dimitri_Bielak_Riches_of_the_Reach.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e6/Dimitri_Bielak_Riches_of_the_Reach.jpg/600px-Dimitri_Bielak_Riches_of_the_Reach.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dimitri_Bielak_Riches_of_the_Reach.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Servants of House Tyrell distribute food to the poor of King's Landing, by Dimitri Bielak © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>After the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tyrell\" title=\"House Tyrell\">House Tyrell</a> brings one hundred wayns laden with <a href=\"/index.php/Food\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Food\">food</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> each day.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a> gives the command of the baggage train of his army to Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Wendel_Manderly\" title=\"Wendel Manderly\">Wendel Manderly</a> when they depart from <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a> for the <a href=\"/index.php/Twins\" title=\"Twins\">Twins</a> to attend the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">wedding</a> of his uncle, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Edmure_Tully\" title=\"Edmure Tully\">Edmure Tully</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Roslin_Frey\" title=\"Roslin Frey\">Roslin Frey</a>. The train is composed of a procession of wayns laden with food, fodder, camp supplies, and wedding gifts. The heavy rain renders the journey very slow. Half the wayns are abandoned to the muck, and their loads distributed amongst mules and draft <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horses</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">Sandor Clegane</a> steals a wayn from a farmer, and uses it to infiltrate the Twins with <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">Red Wedding</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Two wayns are used to transport <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">Maester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Aemon\">Aemon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Gilly\" title=\"Gilly\">Gilly</a> and her <a href=\"/index.php/Monster\" title=\"Monster\">son</a>, as well as provisions for the journey from <a href=\"/index.php/Castle_Black\" title=\"Castle Black\">Castle Black</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Eastwatch-by-the-Sea\" title=\"Eastwatch-by-the-Sea\">Eastwatch-by-the-Sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a> takes forty wayns laden with food when he leaves <a href=\"/index.php/White_Harbor\" title=\"White Harbor\">White Harbor</a> to attend the wedding of <a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Bolton\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ramsay Bolton\">Ramsay Bolton</a> and \"<a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Poole\" title=\"Jeyne Poole\">Arya Stark</a>\" at <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The wayns and wagons of the baggage train of <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a>'s army have difficulty keeping up the pace of the <a href=\"/index.php/March_on_Winterfell\" title=\"March on Winterfell\">march on Winterfell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"<a href=\"http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Wayn\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikt:Wayn\">Wayn</a>\" is an archaic spelling of \"<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wagon\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Wagon\">wain</a>.\"</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wayn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_4\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 4\">Chapter 4</a>, Brienne I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_5\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 5\">Chapter 5</a>, Samwell I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-te